<article>
    <h1>Safe man&#xAD;age&#xAD;ment mea&#xAD;sures re&#xAD;quired for at&#xAD;trac&#xAD;tions re-open&#xAD;ing in phase 2</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200912/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-09-12"><time>2020-09-12</time></a>
        - <span>CLASSIFIED&#xAD;S</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>At­trac­tions such as Univer­sal Stu­dios Sin­ga­pore (USS) and the Sin­ga­pore Zoo have re­opened, with a num­ber of safety mea­sures in place so that vis­i­tors feel safe while hav­ing a good time as well.</p>
    <p>In or­der for an at­trac­tion to be deemed safe for re-open­ing, they must show how the they will achieve all the fol­low­ing out­comes:</p>
    <p>A. Abil­ity to meet den­sity re­quire­ments</p>
    <p>• Limit Ca­pac­ity: Re-open at no more than 25% of op­er­at­ing ca­pac­ity. At­trac­tions which have proven able to im­ple­ment their Safe Man­age­ment Mea­sures ef­fec­tively and con­sis­tently may be al­lowed to in­crease op­er­at­ing ca­pac­ity pro­gres­sively in Phase 2. They will, how­ever, first need to sub­mit ad­di­tional plans to han­dle in­creased ca­pac­ity and ob­tain MTI’s fur­ther ap­proval to do so. • Ex­cep­tions to the 25% cap can be made on a case-by-case ba­sis by MTI if the at­trac­tion can demon­strate that the risk is in­her­ently mit­i­gated by the na­ture of ac­tiv­i­ties and the way vis­i­tors and staff in­ter­act at the at­trac­tion.</p>
    <p>B. Abil­ity to meet sep­a­ra­tion re­quire­ments</p>
    <p>• Im­ple­ment ≥1m dis­tanc­ing be­tween vis­i­tors (ex­cept within a group of vis­i­tors from the same co­hort)</p>
    <p>• Where not fea­si­ble or prac­ti­cal to ap­ply one me­tre dis­tanc­ing be­tween in­di­vid­u­als, to en­sure one me­tre dis­tanc­ing be­tween groups (of not more than 5 pax), and with no mix­ing be­tween groups.</p>
    <p>C. Abil­ity to dis­perse crowds and pre­vent bunch­ing D. Fa­cil­i­tate con­tact trac­ing</p>
    <p>• Put in place manda­tory apps (i.e. Safe En­try)</p>
    <p>• En­cour­age use of TraceTo­gether</p>
    <p>E. Im­ple­ment rig­or­ous clean­ing and dis­in­fect­ing regimes, par­tic­u­larly for high touch el­e­ments</p>

